There's 6 people on a ship

175
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:18,886
我只是个医疗博士,
所以请原谅我问一个愚蠢的问题
I'm just a medical doctor here,
so forgive me if this is a stupid question

176
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:21,097
如果他们走进时空门
If they just step to the event horizon

177
00:11:21,138 --> 00:11:23,516
当门关闭的时候,
他们不能回到飞船控制台吗?
wouldn't they come through to the front
part of the ship, when the gate shuts down?

178
00:11:23,558 --> 00:11:25,810
飞船前面一段不能被重组
The front half won't rematerialise on this side.

179
00:11:25,852 --> 00:11:28,604
时空门只能传送完整物体
The Stargate transmits the matter in discreet units

180
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:31,190
飞船前面一段不能被重组,
The front half of the ship cannot rematerialise,

181
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:34,110
除非整个飞船都通过时空门
Until the whole ship has crossed
into the event horizon

182
00:11:34,151 --> 00:11:36,821
时空门只能接受没有中断的介质
The Stargate is a century waiting for
the contiguous components

183
00:11:36,863 --> 00:11:38,781
也就是说飞船和里面所有的东西
Meaning the jumper and everyone inside

184
00:11:38,823 --> 00:11:41,284
在我们传送他们之前,
必须都通过了时空门
To enter completely,
before we can transport them

185
00:11:42,702 --> 00:11:45,204
他的意思是说时空门只能传送一阵个物体
He say's, the gate only sends
things through in one piece.

186
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,080
我听明白了
Yeah, sorry

187
00:11:46,122 --> 00:11:49,792
很不幸, 直到分子重组完成之前
Unfortunately, the upgoing Stargate
won't transmit the matter stream

188
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:52,211
上传的时空门是不会传送任何流状介质的
until the demolecularization is completed

189
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:53,504
当门关闭的时候
When he shuts down

190
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:57,508
整个飞船前身, 还有里面所有的人都会消失
entire forward section, along with
the men inside will cease to exist

191
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,010
其他人呢?
And what about the others?

192
00:11:59,051 --> 00:12:02,305
飞船会在瞬间沿着时空门被切割
The ship will be severed instantaneously
along the event horizon

193
00:12:02,346 --> 00:12:04,807
他们将被抛向真空宇宙,
They'll be exposed to hard vacuum,

194
00:12:04,849 --> 00:12:06,309
现在还有29分钟
In 29 minutes

195
00:12:09,687 --> 00:12:11,480
他们如果关闭后舱门呢?
What if they close the bulkhead door?

196
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:15,902
整个飞船后部会是密闭的,
起到了一个救生艇的作用
The rear portion of the ship,
will remain pressurised. Become a sort of lifeboat.

197
00:12:15,943 --> 00:12:17,403
他们很快就没有氧气了
It will lose atmosphere very quickly

198
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:19,405
那么我们就有时间派另一个飞船去接他们了
It could buy enough time to send
a second Jumper.

199
00:12:19,447 --> 00:12:20,114
那又怎么样?
And do what?

200
00:12:20,156 --> 00:12:20,990
有办法了!
Figure it out!

201
00:12:21,032 --> 00:12:23,492
和探险者1号取得联系
告诉他们这个建议
Contact Jumper One and made recommendation

202
00:12:42,845 --> 00:12:44,388
你干什么?
What are you doing?

203
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:46,098
对不起
Sorry, here

204
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:48,684
探险者1号, 我是基地
Jumper One, this is Atlantis

205
00:12:48,726 --> 00:12:49,602
我听到了
We're still here.

206
00:12:49,644 --> 00:12:51,521
<i>我们建议你们关闭后舱门</i>
<i>We recommend closing the bulkhead door.</i>

207
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:53,481
哦... 好主意
Oh... Good thinking

208
00:12:53,523 --> 00:12:54,899
然后呢?
What else?

209
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:57,610
我们还在想办法
再和你联系
We are still working on the problem.
We'll get back to you.

210
00:12:57,652 --> 00:12:58,819
完毕
Atlantis base out.

211
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:00,321
谢谢你和我们联系!
Thanks for calling!

212
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:05,493
除了我还有人怕黑吗?
Somebody else is claustrophobic
or is it just me?

213
00:13:05,535 --> 00:13:06,702
为什么关闭舱门?
Why did you close the doors?

214
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:08,788
当时空门关闭,
飞船前部被割断的时候,
So that when the Stargate is close down,
and the forward section is severed,

215
00:13:08,829 --> 00:13:10,706
我们就不会被抛向外太空了
we're not directly exposed to space

216
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:11,499
这门结实吗?
Will it hold?

217
00:13:11,541 --> 00:13:13,876
用潜水艇材质做的,
我想可以...
Like a screen door in a submarine,
I just prefer apoxia...

218
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:14,919
...起到减压的作用
...to decompression.

219
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:16,420
这... 这只是个人想法
It is... it is a personal thing

220
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:18,548
快没空气了
我看你还是冷静点吧
The air's gonna get thin in here.
Your really do have to calm down.

221
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:20,216
- 哦, 如果不这么做27分钟以后你就知道什么是缺氧了
- McKay
- Oh, you wait and see how thin it get's in 27 minutes.
- McKay

222
00:13:20,258 --> 00:13:22,301
真空的宇宙. 那才叫缺氧
Vacuum. That's thin.

223
00:13:22,343 --> 00:13:23,302
把门打开
Knock it off

224
00:13:23,344 --> 00:13:26,389
哦, 我觉得只有我认识到了我们现在处境多危险!
Oh, I apologise for being the only person
who truly comprehends how screwed we are!

225
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:29,392
别和我谈危险!
Don't talk to me about screwed!

226
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:40,278
我们不应该放弃Markham和Stackhouse
And let's not give up on
Markham and Stackhouse, either.

227
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:43,698
我们还有很多时间想办法,
There's plenty of time to solve this thing,

228
00:13:43,739 --> 00:13:47,702
首先你最好闭上嘴,
好好动动脑子
but you've gotta stop using your mouth,
and start using your brain.

229
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:53,207
对不起...我只是...
I'm sorry...I'm just...

230
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:57,211
这是人到生死关头的正常反映
我知道这样不对..
I react to certain doom, in a certain way.
It's a bad habit and..

231
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,089
也许有办法手动让推进器收回
Maybe there is a way to manually
retract the mechanism.

232
00:14:00,131 --> 00:14:01,591
我想应该可以
Yeah maybe there is.

233
00:14:07,597 --> 00:14:09,098
给你这个
Here

234
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:14,020
你很坚强
You seem stronger

235
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:16,314
不. 只是现在不那么疼了
No.it's just the pains not so bad now.

236
00:14:16,355 --> 00:14:17,315
很好
That's good

237
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:18,900
不, 我不觉得
No, It isn't

238
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:20,401
因为我的腿没知觉了
I can't feel my legs

239
00:14:21,986 --> 00:14:23,487
手和胳膊都是麻的
The hands and the arms are numb

240
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:25,281
我基本不能动了
I can barely move them.

241
00:14:25,615 --> 00:14:28,117
我快失去知觉了. 少尉
feelings creeping me out. Look lieutenant

242
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:31,120
我只想告诉你
What I'm trying to say

243
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:33,623
如果我不能把这东西取下去
is if you don't get this damn thing off me.

244
00:14:34,707 --> 00:14:37,001
我会比你先死
I have even less time than you do.

245
00:14:56,521 --> 00:14:57,730
Zelenka博士
Doctor Zelenka

246
00:14:58,814 --> 00:15:01,609
对不起我没有参加会议,
Weir博士, 我实在没有时间
Apologise to not attending a breefing,
Dr Weir, there was not time.

247
00:15:01,609 --> 00:15:03,694
我不想妨碍你
但是我想知道你在做什么
I don't want to slow you down but
I need to know what you're working on

248
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:05,738
这样我可以告诉探险者1号
so I can communicate it to the team
on Jumper one.

249
00:15:05,738 --> 00:15:08,616
我们正在努力 ...
We are attempting to retract the ...

250
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:14,080
把推进器收回到飞船后舱
the drive pod back into the fuse lodge
from inside the rear compartment

251
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:15,206
有什么进展了吗?
Anything yet?

252
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:17,583
远古科技很复杂
There is much redundancy
in the ancient technology.

253
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:20,920
所以我先在这里做个试验
Making it dangerous for them
to experiment with it in this way.

254
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:24,090
也就是说飞船后门有可能打开
他们就被抛向外太空
So they might accidentally open the rear
hatch or shut life support off entirely.

255
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:25,591
是的, 是的, 没错
Yes, yes, yes

256
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:29,595
这就是为什么我要先做个试验
It's just why we're attempting to isolate
the correct control pathway.

257
00:15:29,887 --> 00:15:31,597
明白了. 我有什么能帮上忙的?
Understood. What can I do to help?

258
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:33,975
别和我聊天就行了
Stop talking, please.

259
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:43,401
少尉,
Lieutenant,

260
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:46,028
拿刀把这东西切开
get your knife out and cut this damn thing off.

261
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:48,072
这回他不能在怎么伤到我了
It can't hurt as much as it did last time.

262
00:15:48,114 --> 00:15:49,991
上次你差点死了
The last time, we almost lost you

263
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:51,784
算了, 我怎么样都会死的
Ah well.you're going to lose me anyway

264
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:52,994
长官
Sir

265
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:55,913
我们回到飞船上的时候已经试过切掉它了
We tried to cut it off when
we were back on the planet

266
00:15:55,913 --> 00:15:58,082
各种方法都试了
We tried everything

267
00:15:58,082 --> 00:15:59,584
长官你能坚持吧?
You're right sir?

268
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:03,004
准备好了
Here we go.

269
00:16:11,304 --> 00:16:13,097
任何办法只会让能更难受
Everything we did just seemed to hurt you more.

270
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,974
我想它可以自我治疗
I think it just heals itself.

271
00:16:16,100 --> 00:16:18,394
它吸收你的能量, 就像那些幽灵
it feeds on your strengh, like the Wraith

272
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:20,396
你和我说过了
You had to say that.

273
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:23,858
我父亲给我讲过许多关于这种生物的故事
My father often told stories about
creatures such like this.

274
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:27,904
我一直以为他想让我们这些孩子呆在营地
I always thought he was just trying to keep
the children from straying far from our camp.

275
00:16:28,321 --> 00:16:31,407
很好, 他告诉过你怎么杀了他们吗?
Great, and did he
tell you how to kill it?

276
00:16:31,407 --> 00:16:33,409
我不知道,
我确信我们杀不了它
I don't know sir,
I'm sure we can't.

277
00:16:33,409 --> 00:16:35,703
我想到了另一个办法
I could use a second opinion

278
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:37,496
和基地取得联系
Get back on the radio

279
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:41,292
收到
Affirmative

280
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:43,377
过来吧长官, 接通了
Come here Sir, this micro is open.

281
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:47,089
我是Beckett医生, 伤员怎么样?
This is doctor Beckett, how is our patient?

282
00:16:47,089 --> 00:16:50,384
<i>我是Ford. Sheppard少校苏醒了</i>
<i>但是那个生物还在他身上</i>
<i>This if ford. Major Sheppard is conscious</i>
<i>but the creature is still latched on to him.</i>

283
00:16:50,384 --> 00:16:52,595
大夫能不能来就诊啊?
How do you feel about house calls doc?

284
00:16:52,595 --> 00:16:56,390
我也想
但是你实在太远了
Would if I could major Sheppard but
you'll have to settle for long distance.

285
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:58,809
我听说有东西附在你身上了
I'm told you have something of a cling-on

286
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:03,981
很可笑吧
It's funny

287
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:07,109
是你见过最丑陋的东西了
It's like the ugliest damn thing you've ever seen.

288
00:17:07,109 --> 00:17:09,403
它怎么攻击到你的?
How did it attack yourself ?

289
00:17:09,403 --> 00:17:11,489
我们在回飞船的路上
Well, we returned toward the Jumper

290
00:17:12,698 --> 00:17:14,492
幽灵们向我们开枪
The Wraith were shooting us

291
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:18,913
我掩护你
你去告诉Marco准备起飞
Go tell Marco to get ready for
take off I'll cover you.

292
00:17:18,913 --> 00:17:19,580
你怎么办?
What about you?

293
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,374
我这就回去, 快走!
I'll be there in a minute, GO!

294
00:17:52,697 --> 00:17:55,199
<i>少校回飞船的路被截住了</i>
<i>Major we're cut off from the jumper</i>

295
00:17:56,117 --> 00:17:56,909
不行
Negative

296
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,412
有一个在你3点钟位置
另外两个被我引过来了
They're should be one at your three o'clock
I drew the other two this way

297
00:17:59,412 --> 00:18:01,414
<i>我们被包围了
他们从哪出来的?</i>
<i>They're all around us where'd they come from?</i>

298
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:04,083
少尉你应该知道他们能够隐身的,
Ltd you know how they can make you
see things that aren't there,

299
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:07,086
你前面现在没有人, 赶紧跑!
The path in front of you is cleared, now move!

300
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:15,303
你能描述一下吗?
Can you describe it to me?

301
00:18:15,303 --> 00:18:16,387
好的
Yes sir.

302
00:18:16,387 --> 00:18:20,391
包括尾巴它一共2英尺长,
还有点什么东西在他胳膊下面
It's about two feet in length including the tail,
there's rough stuff under his arm picks

303
00:18:20,892 --> 00:18:24,687
有两个带刺的东西在少校脖子上
靠近颈动脉
It's got two sharp spiny things in his neck
near the Major's carotid artery

304
00:18:24,687 --> 00:18:26,189
描述的再细致点
I need more than that, son

305
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:29,192
4条像腿的东西
Four legs, if you can call them that

306
00:18:29,192 --> 00:18:32,486
紧紧的包住了少校的喉咙
They're wrapped around the Major's throat.

307
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:34,488
找不到眼睛
I can't see any eyes

308
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:39,202
有很坚硬的外壳, 但是肚子下面很松软
It's got a real hard shell, but there's
a soft meaty part underneath.

309
00:18:39,202 --> 00:18:41,787
少校, 你有什么感觉?
Major, what are your physical symptoms?

310
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:44,290
就好像用刀刺我的眼
Well, first it was as a knife in the eye

311
00:18:44,290 --> 00:18:47,502
因为我现在没有什么知觉了
Since I have lost all the feelings
in my extremities

312
00:18:47,502 --> 00:18:49,212
我不能动
I can't move

313
00:18:49,212 --> 00:18:53,216
这么说初期感到疼痛
So it incapacitates first with pain and prophases.

314
00:18:53,508 --> 00:18:56,719
我想去帮McKay检查机器故障
I need to be able to move around
and help McKay with mechanical problem.

315
00:18:56,719 --> 00:19:00,097
如果不想办法
Marco和Stackhouse会死的
Marco and Stackhouse are dead if I don't.

316
00:19:00,097 --> 00:19:01,516
你们都试过什么办法了?
What have you tryed?

317
00:19:01,516 --> 00:19:05,019
试过用刀切, 用火烧,
我甚至用枪打它
I've tried to cut it off, I've tried to burn it off,
I've even tried to shoot it off.

318
00:19:05,019 --> 00:19:07,396
很近的点射
9 mil point blank.

319
00:19:07,396 --> 00:19:09,982
除了差点杀了少校以外,
没有任何效果
Not much worse I can do without
killing the Major along with it.

320
00:19:09,982 --> 00:19:13,319
我相信这个生物属于那些幽灵
I believe the creature is related
in some way to the Wraith

321
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:13,986
真的?
really ?

322
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:14,820
为什么这么说?
How so?

323
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:18,783
它不断吸Sheppard少校的血来维持生命
it feeds itself after each intent to remove him
by sucking life from Major Sheppard

324
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:20,910
和那些幽灵一样
Just as the Wraith would.

325
00:19:22,203 --> 00:19:23,788
我估计是幽灵放出了什么东西
Well, I suppose the Wraith has
to have evolved of something

326
00:19:23,788 --> 00:19:26,582
我估计是一种...
史前的某种东西
I suppose that it is a sort of a...
prehistoric cousin.

327
00:19:29,293 --> 00:19:30,920
大夫听着, 少校不能这样下去
Listen Doctor, the Major can't be worse

328
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:32,713
我们要想点办法
We gonna do something right now

329
00:19:33,714 --> 00:19:37,718
你刚刚说这个生物的腹部很软而且他还吸血
You said that the creature had a underside
an exposed  soft tissue like a leech

330
00:19:38,094 --> 00:19:39,595
我试过把它割开
I tried to cut into it.

331
00:19:39,595 --> 00:19:41,514
那东西差点杀死少校
the thing practically strangled him to death

332
00:19:41,514 --> 00:19:45,518
你不要切掉它
在它身上洒点盐
Son you don't cut leeches off.
You pour salt on to them.

333
00:19:46,018 --> 00:19:48,312
如果你启动磁场他们都会死
If you activate the field they'll die.

334
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:50,565
如果他们解决了这个问题
我们可以一起打开磁场
We can always open it together
if they fix the problem

335
00:19:50,606 --> 00:19:51,607
他们没有时间了
Well they may not have time.

336
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:53,693
如果不这么做他们会毁掉这个设备
If they don't, we could destroy this facility.

337
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:56,487
我是想让你们想个解决方法
It's supposed we're working on solutions.

338
00:19:59,282 --> 00:20:03,202
我们估计飞船一开始就损坏了
